LAFIA – The State High Court 2 sitting in Lafia the Nasarawa State capital, presided over by Justice Simon Aboki, has fixed May 5, 2022 to visit a disputed land said to belong to Gbenda Igbaa Aken Family alleged to have been taken over by Aliko Dangote and group of companies. The Ojila/Gbenda Igba Akeen of Tunga district in Awe Local Government Area of Nasara­wa has asked the court to stop Aliko Dangote and Companies for further encroachment into their farm land and destruction of their ancestral grave. In a case file No. NSD/ LF 122/2021, the plaintiff prayed to the court to collect back their three hundred hectares of land for them. When the case came hearing bothpartiesfiledaninterlocutory injunction as two motions were mentioned for the extension of time brought in by the first de­fendant. Counsel to plaintiff, Barr. Ste­phen Akpehe averred that both the counsel to Dangote Sugar company and counsel to third defendant, the Nasarawa State government had been allowed to file motion defending their matter. He further explained that the plaintiffs were denied the N200 million promised to be given to the affected persons in those communities by Dangote as part of his social responsibility but his plaintiffs were denied the token. He further explained that Dan­gote promised to come back and negotiate settlement, compensation to the plaintiff again none of them benefited.